        <body>
            <pb n="1" facs="../images/26579_1.png" />
            <div type="correspondence-action">
                <head rendition="#center">
                    <name type="person">Stephen A Chase</name><lb />
                    <placeName>Salem</placeName>
                    <date when="1854-01-19">Jan 19 '54</date>
                </head>
            </div>
            <pb n="2" facs="../images/26579_2.png" /> 
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#indent3">
                        <placeName>Salem</placeName>
                        <date when="1854-01-12">First month 12th. 1854</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My Dear Friend <lb />
                        <name rendition="#indent2">Robert <unclear>I.</unclear> Murray</name>
                    </salute>
                </opener>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p rendition="#indent">
                    I take the liberty of <lb />
                    giving the bearer <persName ref="psn:peter_still" resp="#FG">Peter Still</persName> a letter to thee. - He is <lb />
                    the colored man, whose story I partly related <lb />
                    to thee in <placeName resp="#FG">Boston</placeName>. - 
                </p>
                <p rendition="#indent">
                    I think there is that in his story that <lb />
                    verifies the proverb that "truth is stranger <lb />
                    than fiction."
                </p>
                <p rendition="#indent">
                    I do not doubt the truthfulness of Peter <lb />
                    and he can tell thee his own story, which <lb />
                    unfolds a phase in the history of slavery <lb />
                    strongly illustrative of its evils, it oppressions,<lb />
                    its injustice and its opposition to all that is <lb />
                    good and kind and Christian.
                </p>
                <p rendition="#indent">
                    I have ventured to tell Peter that I think <lb />
                    he will find sympathizing friends in <placeName resp="#FG">New York</placeName> <lb />
                    and among them the kind friend I now address.
                </p>
                <p rendition="#indent">
                    My wife desires to be kindly remembered <lb />
                    to thee with love to thy wife. - We remember <lb />
                    with pleasure thy too short call upon us in <lb />
                    the autumn - Please remember me respectfully <lb />
                    to thy wife and believe me
                </p>
            </div>
                <closer>
                    <salute rendition="#indent2">Thy sincere friend, </salute>
                    <signed rendition="#indent3"> Stephen A. Chase</signed>
                </closer>
        </body>
